The paper focuses on improving the effectiveness of test suites for dynamic analysis techniques, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The proposed technique involves refactoring test suites, which involves modifying the structure of the code, making it relevant to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the application of the technique to exception contracts, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY). The experimental results involve the fixing of bugs, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
